"Deroin J.-P., Condom T.","Small mountain glacier shrinkage at the century time-scale: an example in the French western Alps [Retrait séculaire des glaciers locaux de montagne : un exemple dans les Alpes occidentales françaises]",2007,"Comptes Rendus - Geoscience","339","7",,"449","459",,,10.1016/j.crte.2007.05.002,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-34547595632&partnerID=40&md5=743fbbc973068ed31ffa443d7725f276","Observation de la Terre et information géographique, Institut francilien des sciences appliquées, Université de Marne-la-Vallée, 5, boulevard Descartes, Champs-sur-Marne, 77454 Marne-la-Vallee cedex 2, France; EA GHYMAC no 4134, institut EGID-Bordeaux-3, université Michel-de-Montaigne, 1, allée Fernand-Daguin, 33607 Pessac cedex, France","Deroin, J.-P., Observation de la Terre et information géographique, Institut francilien des sciences appliquées, Université de Marne-la-Vallée, 5, boulevard Descartes, Champs-sur-Marne, 77454 Marne-la-Vallee cedex 2, France; Condom, T., EA GHYMAC no 4134, institut EGID-Bordeaux-3, université Michel-de-Montaigne, 1, allée Fernand-Daguin, 33607 Pessac cedex, France","This paper reports on small mountain glacier variations in the northern Belledonne region (French Alps). Between 1926 and 2006, the evolution is surveyed using remote-sensing techniques. Then, it is correlated with climate data for the same period. In the late 1920s and in 1980, there was a maximum extent of the glaciers. The 1980 surge is due to high precipitations during the late 1970s, a similar trend being punctually observed in 1993. Between 1980 and 2003, the Rocher Blanc glaciers have strongly receded, their total surface being divided by ten. From 1997 onward, the large retreat can be explained by the increase of the mean daily temperature, especially the minimum daily temperature. Moreover, unusually high temperatures have been registered during the summer 2003 heat wave. Small mountain glaciers appear to be more sensitive to climate change than larger ones. Their surfaces change within 6 to 12 months. © 2007.","Belledonne; France; Glacier; Global climate change; Remote sensing","climate change; glacier dynamics; global climate; ice retreat; remote sensing; shrinkage; timescale; valley glacier; Alps; Eurasia; Europe; France; Western Alps; Western Europe",,,,,,"Bauder, A., Hoelzle, M., Les glaciers des Alpes suisses en 2000/2001 (2002) Les Alpes, 10, pp. 24-29; Bauder, A., Schär, C., Blatter, H., Les glaciers des Alpes suisses en 2001/2002 et 2002/2003 (2004) Les Alpes, 10, pp. 30-39; Bauder, A., Vieli, A., Hoelzle, M., Les glaciers des Alpes suisses en 1999/2000 (2001) Les Alpes, 10, pp. 22-31; Benn, D.I., Owen, L.A., Osmaston, H.A., Seltzer, G.O., Porter, S.C., Mark, B., Reconstruction of equilibrium-line altitudes for tropical and sub-tropical glaciers (2005) Quat. Int., 138-139, pp. 8-21; Berthier, E., Arnaud, Y., Baratoux, D., Vincent, C., Rémy, F., Recent rapid thinning of the 'Mer de Glace' glacier derived from satellite optical images (2004) Geophys. Res. Lett., 31 (L17401), pp. 1-4; Böhm, R., Auer, I., Brunetti, M., Maugeri, M., Nanni, T., Schöner, W., Regional temperature variability in the European Alps 1760-1998 (2001) Int. J. Climatol., 21, pp. 1779-1801; Chueca, J., Julián, A., Relationship between solar radiation and the development and morphology of small cirque glaciers (Maladeta Mountain massif, Central Pyrenees, Spain) (2004) Geografiska Annaler, Ser. A86, pp. 81-89; Dessens, J., Bücher, A., Changes in minimum and maximum temperatures at the Pic du Midi in relation with humidity and cloudiness, 1882-1984 (1995) Atmos. Res., 37, pp. 147-162; Dyurgerov, M.B., Meier, M.F., Twentieth century climate change: Evidence from small glaciers (2000) Proc. Natl Acad. Sci. USA, 97, pp. 1406-1411; Easterling, D.R., Horton, B., Jones, P.D., Peterson, T.C., Karl, T.R., Parker, D.E., Salinger, M.J., Folland, C.K., Maximum and minimum temperature trends for the globe (1997) Science, 277, pp. 364-36